{{ill|Takiribime|ja|タキリビメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takiribime|en:draft|}} (Lady Mist) is a [[Kunitsukami]]. She is the daughter of [[Susanoo]].<ref name="國學院大學デジタルミュージアム">{{Cite web|title=Encyclopedia of Shinto詳細|url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/?id=9149|access-date=2024-03-24|website=國學院大學デジタルミュージアム|language=ja}}</ref> The [[Shinsen Shōjiroku]] describes her as a [[Kunitsukami]] and many clans as descended from her.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Takiribime • . A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |url=https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/takiribime/ |access-date=2023-10-21 |website=. A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |language=en-GB}}</ref>  

She was moved from [[Tashima Shrine]] to [[Munakata Taisha]], so that shrine is called Moto-Munakata.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wp4xhRXsARcC&dq=Tashima+Shrine&pg=PA47|title=Fishing Villages in Tokugawa, Japan|last=Kalland|first=Arne|date=1995-01-01|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=978-0-8248-1632-2|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pcjZDwAAQBAJ&dq=Tashima+Shrine&pg=PT104|title=Sacred Heritage in Japan|last1=Rots|first1=Aike P.|last2=Teeuwen|first2=Mark|date=2020-04-02|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-000-04563-5|language=en}}</ref>{{Page needed|date=December 2023}}

{{ill|Takiribime|ja|タキリビメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takiribime|en:draft|}} is described as marrying [[Ōkuninushi|Ōkuninushi]] which links the {{ill|Munakata clan|ja|宗像氏|simple|User:Immanuelle/Munakata_clan|ja|宗像氏}} in with the {{ill|Izumo clan|en|4=simple|5=User:Immanuelle/Izumo clan}} in myth and the establishment of [[Munakata Taisha]] and [[Izumo-taisha]].<ref name="國學院大學デジタルミュージアム" />
