[[fr:Takiribime]][[original pages]][[simple:user:immanuelle/Takiribime]] [[Category:Link complete]] [[Category:Completion tier 2]] [[Category:qq---qq]] [[Category:Tagorihime]] {{afc comment|1=some history at [[every:takiribime]] but not much[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 05:52, 18 February 2025 (UTC)}} {{Infobox deity | type = Shinto | father = [[Susanoo]] | cult_centre = [[Munakata Taisha]][[en:Tagorihime]] | siblings = {{ill|Tagitsuhime|ja|タギツヒメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Tagitsuhime|en:draft||fr}}, {{ill|Ichikishimahime|ja|イチキシマヒメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Ichikishimahime|en:draft||fr}} | children = [[Ajisukitakahikone]], {{ill|Shitateruhime|ja|シタテルヒメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Shitateruhime|en:draft||fr}} |spouse=[[Ōkuninushi|Ōkuninushi]]<ref name="國學院大學デジタルミュージアム" />|name=Takiribime|image=File:宗像大社沖津宮.JPG|caption=Okitsu-gū (沖津宮) where she is worshipped at [[Munakata Taisha]] | Hinduism_equivalent = [[Mahakali]] or [[Parvati]] | equivalent1_type = Buddhist | equivalent1 = [[Daikokuten#Goddess Daikokutennyo|Daikokutennyo]] }}
{{complex}}
{{ill|Tagorihime|ja|タキリビメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takiribime|en:draft|}} (Lady Mist) is a {{ill|Kunitsukami|en|4=fr}}. She is one of the three daughters of [[Susanoo]].<ref name="國學院大學デジタルミュージアム">{{Cite web|title=Encyclopedia of Shinto詳細|url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/?id=9149|access-date=2024-03-24|website=國學院大學デジタルミュージアム|language=ja}}</ref> The {{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en}} describes her as a {{ill|Kunitsukami|en|4=fr}} and many clans as descended from her.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Takiribime • . A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |url=https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/takiribime/ |access-date=2023-10-21 |website=. A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史 |language=en-GB}}</ref>
She was moved from [[Tashima Shrine|Tashima Shrine]] to [[Munakata Taisha|Munakata Taisha]], so that shrine is called Moto-Munakata.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wp4xhRXsARcC&dq=Tashima+Shrine&pg=PA47|title=Fishing Villages in Tokugawa, Japan|last=Kalland|first=Arne|date=1995-01-01|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|isbn=978-0-8248-1632-2|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pcjZDwAAQBAJ&dq=Tashima+Shrine&pg=PT104|title=Sacred Heritage in Japan|last1=Rots|first1=Aike P.|last2=Teeuwen|first2=Mark|date=2020-04-02|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-000-04563-5|language=en}}</ref>{{Page needed|date=December 2023}}
{{ill|Tagorihime|ja|タキリビメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takiribime|en:draft||fr||en|Tagorihime}} is described as marrying [[Ōkuninushi|Ōkuninushi]] which links the {{ill|Munakata clan|ja|宗像氏|simple|User:Immanuelle/Munakata_clan|ja|宗像氏|fr|Clan Munakata}} in with the {{ill|Izumo clan|en|4=simple|5=User:Immanuelle/Izumo clan}} in myth and the establishment of [[Munakata Taisha|Munakata Taisha]] and [[Izumo-taisha|Izumo-taisha]].<ref name="國學院大學デジタルミュージアム" /> [[ja:タキリビメ]] [[File:Okinoshima_Munakata_theology.svg|thumb|diagram explaining the structure of [[Munakata Taisha]] and its relationship to theology between the three sisters and [[Sumiyoshi sanjin]] and [[Watatsumi]]]]
All her children are worshipped at {{ill|Shitori Shrine (Tottori)|lt=Shitori Shrine|en|4=fr|5=Shitori-jinja|6=ja|7=倭文神社_(湯梨浜町)|8=simple|9=User:Immanuelle/Shitori Shrine (Tottori)}} alongside those of her sisters, she and her sisters are not. This means a connection might exist but is uncertain.
[[File:Challenge_of_Amaterasu_and_Susanoo-eng.svg|thumb]] == Syncretism == Tagorihime has been identified with [[Parvati]] or [[Durga]] or [[Kali]] in syncretism of the Munakata Goddesses with the Hindu Tridevi. As she is the destroyer and the future, she is the distant final Island of the three shrines.
However this worship is rare and much less common than syncretism of just {{ill|Ichikishimahime|ja|イチキシマヒメ|simple|User:Immanuelle/Ichikishimahime|en:draft||fr}} with Saraswati
== See Also ==
* {{ill|Munakata clan|ja|宗像氏|simple|User:Immanuelle/Munakata_clan|ja|宗像氏|fr|Clan Munakata}}
